ine Dining"],"tags":["Iconic Property","Mughal Style"],"image":{"src":"https://picsum.photos/seed/The%20Himalayan%20Manali/400/280","alt":"The Himalayan Manali"}}],"restaurants":[],"activities":["Sightseeing","Adventure sports","Temple visits","Local markets","Heritage walks","Trekking","Spiritual","Cultural","Nature walks","Wildlife safaris"],"gallery":[{"src":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a4/Manali_to_Rohtang_Pass_04.jpg/1280px-Manali_to_Rohtang_Pass_04.jpg","alt":"Manali photo 1"},{"src":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ad/Manali_to_Rohtang_Pass_01.jpg/1280px-Manali_to_Rohtang_Pass_01.jpg","alt":"Manali photo 2"},{"src":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7f/Bouldering_in_Solang_Valley_-_Manali%2C_India.jpg/1280px-Bouldering_in_Solang_Valley_-_Manali%2C_India.jpg","alt":"Manali photo 3"},{"src":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/A_view_of_solang_valley_on_the_way_to_rohtang_pass.jpg/1280px-A_view_of_solang_valley_on_the_way_to_rohtang_pass.jpg","alt":"Manali photo 4"},{"src":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/28/Hadimba_Devi_Temple_Manali.jpg/1280px-Hadimba_Devi_Temple_Manali.jpg","alt":"Manali photo 5"},{"src":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/de/Hadimba_Temple%2C_Himachal_Pradesh.jpg","alt":"Manali photo 6"}],"faq":[{"q":"What is the best time to visit Manali?","a":"The best time to visit Manali is Oct – Jun (avoid Jul–Aug monsoon). Summers are 10–25°C and winters are -10 to 10°C."},{"q":"How do I reach Manali?","a":"The nearest airport is Bhuntar Airport (Kullu), KUU (50 km) and the nearest railway station is Jogindernagar Railway Station (165 km). NH3 is well maintained. Rohtang Pass route needs permit. Roads may close in heavy snow."},{"q":"How many days are enough for Manali?","a":"4 days are usually enough to cover the top attractions of Manali at a relaxed pace."},{"q":"How much does a hotel cost in Manali?","a":"Stays in Manal